main event: An unidentified object was observed in Cupar, Scotland on 24 October 1963. The object was both seen and heard, maneuvering in the sky for about 15-20 minutes.
interesting points: The object made a sound similar to an electrical generator., It was observed through binoculars., The sighting involved two witnesses, including a son and a neighbor., The object was initially stationary before moving at a tremendous speed., The USAF acknowledged the report and included it in their ongoing study of UFOs.
